<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id796be88a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1223"><num value="1223">§ 1223.</num><heading> Limitations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any action brought pursuant to this chapter shall be forever barred unless commenced within three years after the cause of action shall have accrued.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id796be88b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-08/ch1038/s3">Aug. 8, 1956, ch. 1038, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70/1125">70 Stat. 1125</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
